description: Seven appliances attended the scene and it took more than two hours to extinguish.
title: Suffolk fire crews tackle Adastral Park office fire
title_page: Suffolk fire crews tackle Adastral Park office fire - BBC News
maintext:
Firefighters were called to a blaze at an office on a business park.
Crews from Suffolk Fire and Rescue services were called to Adastral Park, in Martlesham, near Ipswich, just after 10:30 GMT.
A spokesperson said the incident was contained quickly, limiting damage from fire and smoke.
Seven appliances attended the scene and the fire was extinguished just before 14:00 GMT.
